<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7111&amp;p=30535#p30535"><![CDATA[
Hi crvst<br /><br />I decided to abandon what I made so far, because if what you really want is near white,<br />then the best skin is Ivo's Windows 8 skin7.<br />It is stuck on transparency 181/255. What I did was make everything same color, <br />and put in your thin scrollbar. That scrollbar created speedbumps, hurdles, and moats filled with sewage.<br />I had to put an option in case someone wants to use skin without menu glass, like on Windows 8.<br />Make sure to set button correctly, or you will see scrollbar's unmentionables.<br /><br />Settings on Windows 10<br />So either put CSM &quot;Glass opacity&quot; setting at 50, or 0. In my opinion 0 is better.<br />Turn on &quot;Overide glass color&quot; option, and set up a white color like 220<br /><br />If you are on Windows 7 there are other menu glass settings to use.<br /><br />If you want to edit the skin bitmaps to lower transparency, everything has to match,<br />like scrollbar parts, and programs background. The thin scroll bar creates the biggest challenges. <br /><br />Anyway I think I'm done. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> It's not going to look like the picture above. <br />Will look more frosty foggy. I still have the old partial finished skins,<br />if somebody wants to continue further with it. I put them in zip.<br /><br />Notes <br />I don't have any knowledge of how to make area on left side of scrollbar thinner.<br />I left the borders the way they are. Is not that hard to edit the bitmaps and selectors to make flat.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Fri Nov 25, 2016 9:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
