<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7111&amp;p=30524#p30524"><![CDATA[
I looked at your new mockup picture. Looks very nice.<br />It will be hard to duplicate that.<br />The whites are still close to white. Very transparent.<br />Unless you are on Win7 using a faint dark text glow in a theme,and heavy fonts, <br />it's going to be hard to see white text on, near white backgrounds.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Ok. I just see you have picked another skin to modify more easily. <br />In that skin, instead of the bitmaps having different alpha value, it's the bitmap mask.<br />The bitmap masks would need to go to an image editor to adjust alpha values, and put back again. <br />Looks like at standard 191 alpha.<br />Hey, maybe black text is better on that menu?<br /><br />This is where it starts to get more complicated. To have transparency, many bitmaps need to be 32 bit alpha bitmaps.<br />Like selectors, program tree background changed to different alpha/color text value. <br />The reason the submenu selector looks very see through, is because it is not a real 32 bit bitmap. <br />It is only 24 bit with that text color.<br />If you want semi transparent scroll bar, most of those parts too, and the search bitmap box. <br />Probably a few more that I forgot.<br /><br />Are you making your skin for Win7, or Win 10?<br /><br />I'm trying to change my test skin to blurred left column. Not working too well on Win 10.<br />If I make it frosty white, cant see white text. If I put in light smokey grey, text is starting to be readable, but now looks dull grey. <br />Adjusting this stuff is really up to the person and the operating system. The blur on Win 7 is more transparency with less blur radius. <br />Win 7 also does not have as much residual glass color. <br />I'll try a little more tonight to see if I can do anything more. <br />Tomorrow night I'll upload the partially complete skin, for you to take parts out. Like the scrollbar parts and reuse.<br />I did increase brightness from 42/255 to 150/255. My taste or rather low contrast eyes are different than yours.<br /><br />Here is picture of it. I have color masks turned off, with small icons. <br />CSM settings have 24 sized small icons. Glass opacity at 0. I never did anything with the submenus.<br />Never used the a menu like this. I got scared of no 2nd column. I had to put a few links in. <br />It's odd having a search column so narrow.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Thu Nov 24, 2016 9:09 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
