<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7111&amp;p=30500#p30500"><![CDATA[
Not sure what I'm looking at in the picture.  <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_neutral.gif" alt=":|" title="Neutral" /> I don't know what a classic skin7 theme is?<br /><br />Is it a 7style menu with entries deleted in second column, with altered slices to cut off second column,<br />or is it full alpha transparency at zero, in second column?<br /><br />Taskbar blur works differently than menu blur.<br /><br />If you want to make second column with blur (fullglass), even without a glass mask, glass color will show at a low level. <br />Turning csm Glass opacity setting to 0 can help reduce glass color further. <br />It would require  modification of 32 bit menu bitmap to make your desired rgb brightness/alpha transparency<br />Could start out with your grey menu color rgb at 45 up to white 255/ transparency could try middle of the road 128 alpha  <br /><br /><br />It would require this text below as well:<br /><br />Main_opacity=glass<br />Main2_opacity=fullglass<br /><br /><br /><br />If you made the scrollbar already - great.<br />If not, it can probably be done, but the width will automatically stretch to make regular size scroll size. <br />You could make the stretching part as dark menu color on left of white area.<br />It would end up with dead space on left between text and white skinny thumb bar.<br /><br />I could be wrong on a lot of what I just said.  <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_surprised.gif" alt=":o" title="Surprised" /> <br /><br />That's about all I can say. Goodnight.<br /><br />Hmm.<br />I guess you changed small icon size to 24?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Wed Nov 23, 2016 9:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
